## Comparative Summary of Responses

| Aspect                    | East Francia                                | England                                   |
|---------------------------|--------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| **Initial Viking Impact** | Raids on coastal towns like Hamburg (845) | Monastery of Lindisfarne attacked (793); large Danish invasion (865) |
| **Military Response**     | Fortresses along coasts; strong cavalry under Louis the German | Fortified towns (burhs); standing army and navy under Alfred the Great |
| **Key Leaders**           | Charlemagne (fortifications); Louis the German (military defense) | Alfred the Great (victory at Edington, Danelaw treaty); Ethelred II (Danegeld, pogroms) |
| **Political Strategy**    | Granting land to Vikings (Normandy) to integrate them | Treaty establishing Danelaw; Christianization of Viking leaders |
| **Outcome**               | Temporary halt of raids; eventual assimilation of Vikings | Partial loss of territory; eventual Danish conquest under Cnut |

